BT 0 g /F2 18 Tf 206.64 740 Td (WHAT IS PANIC DISORDER?) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 730 m 540 730 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 700 Td (Panic disorder is characterized by recurrent, unexpected panic attacks -) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 683 Td (sudden surges of intense fear that reach a peak within minutes.) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 12 Tf 72 650 Td (Common symptoms include:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 625 Td (- Racing or pounding heart) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 607 Td (- Sweating, trembling, or shaking) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 589 Td (- Shortness of breath or feeling smothered) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 571 Td (- Chest pain or discomfort) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 553 Td (- Nausea or stomach distress) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 535 Td (- Dizziness or lightheadedness) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 517 Td (- Chills or hot flashes) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 499 Td (- Numbness or tingling) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 481 Td (- Feeling detached from yourself \(derealization\)) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 463 Td (- Fear of losing control or dying) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 425 Td (Key Point: Panic attacks are NOT dangerous. They are your body's) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 407 Td (fight-or-flight system misfiring. You will NOT die, go crazy, or faint.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
