BT 0 g /F2 18 Tf 198.0 740 Td (THE PANIC CYCLE EXPLAINED) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 730 m 540 730 l S Q
BT 0.1 g /F2 12 Tf 72 700 Td (Understanding the cycle keeps you trapped:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 100 670 Td (1. TRIGGER: A body sensation or situation) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 100 645 Td (2. CATASTROPHIC THOUGHT: 'I'm having a heart attack!') Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 100 620 Td (3. ANXIETY INCREASES: More adrenaline released) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 100 595 Td (4. MORE BODY SENSATIONS: Heart races faster, breathing changes) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 100 570 Td (5. MORE CATASTROPHIC THOUGHTS: 'Something is really wrong!') Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 100 545 Td (6. FULL PANIC ATTACK: Peak fear, intense symptoms) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 100 520 Td (7. AVOIDANCE: You avoid similar situations next time) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 100 495 Td (8. CYCLE STRENGTHENS: Avoidance confirms danger belief) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 80 480 450 250 re S Q
BT 0 g /F2 12 Tf 72 450 Td (BREAKING THE CYCLE:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 425 Td (This workbook targets steps 2 & 7. By changing your interpretation) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 408 Td (of symptoms and facing feared situations, the cycle breaks.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
